Above him danced Bora, a radiant phantom of morning mist whose magnificent, booming songs carried across the heavens. Witnessing Aethel’s quiet despair, Bora descended into the deep, barren ravines. To comfort the silent archivist and protect the mortal realm, she sacrificed her shimmering essence, weaving her powerful voice directly into the canyon bedrock. 

When the Grey Rust surged, Aethel struck the enchanted rock. Instead of a dull thud, Bora’s voice roared from the stone. "We remember!" the mountains thundered in unison, shattering the mist. Today, the beautiful echo remains as Bora's enduring gift to the silent peaks.

